
*** HOW TO USE DADY


> INTRODUCTION

dady is a program that allows users to control robotic nodes (amy, goon, rolybody, ...) from CLI.

It uses tron, tron2 & amy libraries:
- libtron2_coms
- libtron_wire
- libamy_interface
- ...


> INSTALLATION


1. Install tron & tron2 libs

git clone https://github.com/albarral/tron.git
git clone https://github.com/albarral/tron2.git

follow instructions in file howto_install_tron
follow instructions in file howto_install_tron2

2. Build dady project (in Netbeans)

3. Create link to dady executable:
 
cd <desired_folder>
ln -s <tron2_installation_path>/dady/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux/dady dady


> USAGE

usage: dady node topic concept*quantity

user guidance: 
- use "dady" to get all available nodes
- use "dady <node>" to get all available topics for the given node
- use "dady <node> <topic>" to get all available concepts for the given node-topic


> EXAMPLES 

./dady arm axis pan*60.0	(moves arm horizontally to 60.0 degrees position)
./dady arm axis vtilt*10.0	(moves arm vertically at 10 degrees/second) 
./dady arm extra end*1		(ends arm control process)


